#include<iostream> #include<iomanip> #include<string.h> #include<stdlib.h> using namespace std; class University{ private: int id; string name; char sex; public: University(){ id=0; name="NULL"; sex=0; } University(int i,string n,char se){ id=i; name=n; sex=se; } void input(); void output(); }; class Student{ private: static const int MAX=100; int course; int rank; int semester; public: Student(){ course=0; rank=0; semester=0; } Student(int c,int r,int s){ course=c; rank=r; semester=s; } void getdata(); void setdata(); }; void University::input(){ cout << "Enter student id : ";cin >> id; cout << "Enter student name : ";cin >> name; cout << "Enter student sex : ";cin >> sex; } void Student::getdata(){ cout << "Enter student course :$ ";cin >> course; cout << "Enter student rank : ";cin >> rank; cout << "Enter student semester : ";cin >> semester; } void University::output(){ cout<<left<<setw(12)<<id <<setw(12)<<name <<setw(12)<<sex; } void Student::setdata(){ cout<<left<<"$"<<setw(12)<<course <<setw(12)<<rank <<setw(12)<<semester <<endl; } void header(){ cout<<left<<setw(12)<<"ID"<<setw(12)<<"Name"<<setw(12)<<"Sex"<<setw(12)<<"Course"<<setw(12)<<"Rank"<<setw(12)<<"Semester"<<endl; } int main() { static const int MAX=100; University obj[MAX]; Student *stu; int n,i; cout << "Enter the number of students: "; cin >> n; stu = (Student *)malloc(n*sizeof(Student)); for(i=0;i<n;i++){ cout << "Student " << i + 1<< endl; obj[i].input(); stu->getdata(); } header(); for(i=0;i<n;i++){ obj[i].output(); stu->setdata(); } return 0; }
